    </p>
    <p>
        I was born and raised in Missouri, and if you've
        spent any considerable time in the great Mid-West, you know that not only is it a great place to live
        and raise a family, it's also just boring enough to become quite invested in video games from a young
        age. Like many others, I grew up playing all sorts of games, but as I got older, and unlike many others,
        my taste in games didn't really keep up with the times. Looking at a brand new game on a TV nowadays
        doesn't capture the same feelings I had as when I looked at a new game when I was younger. Some people
