    <h1>What is Quaint Gaming?</h1>
    <p>First and foremost, Quaint Gaming is a community. We are what they call "old school" gamers who have played
    our way through the trenches and enjoyed every minute of it. Okay, maybe not every minute. As time goes one, 
    more games are developed and more games get left behind. We don't like to see those games that have stood out
    to us getting left in the dust of the 80s and 90s. Many of those older games are still very playable to this
    day, even to someone who isn't accustomed to playing older games. This website is a way to bring people together
    under a common niche, promoting dialogue, sharing, and playing the great games of history.</p>

    <div class="text-center">
        <img src="~/Content/Images/notforgotten.jpg" />
    </div>

    <h1>What can I do here?</h1>
    <p>What a great question, because there is alot to do here at Quaint Gaming! First, I implore you to sign up to
    become a full member of the website, as there are some things that only members have access to. After filling out
    the registration form, I would then suggest that you to browse the games. If you're not familiar with a title, take note 
    of the game's rating on that game's page. That's the rating given to the game by the users of Quaint Gaming, so you 
    can get an idea of what we think about it. Then hit the comments and see what our users have to say. There, you'll 
    find in-depth reviews, personal accounts, even stories written for that particular title. Feel free to join in on the
    discussion, we welcome all members and encourage interaction. Since you've already registered, in addition to being able
    to take part in the comments section, you've also gained access to one of the site's best features, exclusive only to
    members. You can now download any game that we host, right here on the site, and it's completely free. Now, please 
    keep in mind that we are conscious of the legality behind sharing games that fall under copywrite protection. We hold
    high standards to keep ourselves, and you, within the bounds of the law on Quaint Gaming. But we still have you covered.
    If we dont host a specific game you're after, there's a very high likelihood that you'll find the game for cheap on one 
    of our friend's sites in the Links section. 
    </p>

